body:
#### PR description:

This pull request is made because we want to add, in the CloseByParticleGunProducer Workflow, the possibility to shoot a random number of particles (or a fixed one) chosen randomly from a vector of partIDs set in the snippet. In addition, the particles are shooted in random (phi,R) windows. Now in the configuration file the number of particles should be set, along with a boolean parameter (RandomShoot) which will be used in the producer to select either that number of particles or a random one in the range 1 - NParticles+1.
In addition, the working snippet in the Generators folder has been modified properly.

@rovere 
@felicepantaleo
